cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.MS, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the synthesis of distributed implementations for specifications in Parametric Linear Temporal Logic (PLTL), which involves both logic and distributed systems. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper deals with scheduling assumptions, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
